      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get the \"living in the moment\" thing but it feels so fake. like putting a band-aid on a gaping wound. if the math says it all ends in zero, then the struggle itself is just illogical. why keep playing a game where the score gets reset to nothing anyway? it feels like we're just dragging out the inevitable.",
